@flexiarg relationship-coherence/mutual-coaching
@title Coach Each Other's Becoming
@sigils [🤝/勵]
@keywords coaching, job-applications, outreach, proofreading, accountability, positive-peer-pressure, fellow-freelancer, reciprocity
@audience correspondents who are also each other's work allies
@references [relationship-coherence/parallel-lives-mirroring relationship-coherence/held-uncertainty]
@references-extra ["Instance of origin: 2026-04-30 — after Julia asks about rates, Joe advises concretely ('£100 per hour including reading time... not unreasonable for consulting') and Julia: 'it's really helpful to talk to a fellow freelancer! 🙏' Recurs as reciprocal drafting (2026-06-07 Julia line-edits Joe's Anthropic essay; 2026-06-14 Joe runs Julia's cover letter through Claude) and accountability ('positive peer pressure', 2026-06-02)."]
@tone practical
@style pattern

! conclusion: When one faces a work, money, or outreach decision, coach concretely, reciprocate with your own drafts, and nudge each other into action ('positive peer pressure') — from the shared identity of fellow freelancers.

  + context: Both careers are precarious and self-directed; the relationship doubles as a two-person guild. Job applications, rates, cold-outreach emails, and reach-outs are drafted, proofread, and chased jointly.

  + IF:
    one of you is drafting an application, weighing a rate, or hesitating on a scary reach-out.

  + HOWEVER:
    coaching must stay reciprocal and non-managerial — one-way advice becomes a hierarchy, and nudging becomes pressure if it overrides the other's capacity (see relationship-coherence/capacity-honoring).

  + THEN:
    give concrete, specific help; share your own draft in return; and offer accountability ('shall we peer-pressure each other?') so the scary step actually gets taken.

  + BECAUSE:
    two precarious vocations cheered and coached in parallel are more survivable than one; reciprocal, concrete help turns an open horizon (relationship-coherence/held-uncertainty) into doable next steps and affirms 'we are in this together'.

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    - This is the active, career-facing sibling of relationship-coherence/parallel-lives-mirroring: not just noticing the symmetry but working it.
